&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role: Dental Nurse, Fixed Term&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grade: 4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to: Clinic Team Leader&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peninsula Dental Social Enterprise is seeking a motivated, committed, enthusiastic person to fill a Dental Nurse position in Truro.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for working efficiently within the Dental Education Facility, supporting undergraduate dental students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A recognised Dental Nurse qualification and a current GDC registration are essential for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary starting point is pro rata to £21,328 - £23,889 (actual pay £14,281.30 - £15,996.16)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4 days a week, 38 weeks per year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is a fixed term contract for 6 months. This will be reviewed and the contract may be extended or become permanent dependent on operational requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peninsula Dental Social Enterprise provides dental services and education from four teaching clinics across the southwest, from Exeter to Truro. The company supports the work of the University of Plymouth Peninsula Dental School training the Dentists and Therapists of tomorrow. As a Social Enterprise, we are focused on providing benefits to the communities we serve locally, including patients, students and the wider community requiring oral healthcare and education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An enhanced DBS check will be completed.&lt;/p&gt;
